It's time to completely renovate the bedroom. This is the last room in the house that has only been simply decorated.
Remove the ugly electric fireplace and grate. Seal the chimney, replace the damaged plaster, and repaint. Custom make a closet.
We usually start with a rough pencil sketch...
The messy phase is over.
A few dead birds were found behind the flue, all dried out :(
Prepare for next week's painter
I'm happy with the small niche next to it
Put the new closet here (we haven't even started designing it yet 🙈)
Ha ha, check what we found behind the radiator!
We still remember adding cute little ventilation holes to prevent the chimney from getting damp
Sweep installed the chimney cap and the top of the chimney. Those crows that like to build nests in the chimney should be safer now 🪺
The plasterers are done. We'll lay the flooring tomorrow!
The cork mats are in place, and we even rolled toilet paper into a dust collector for the vacuum cleaner to suck up sawdust. 😂
Part of the floor has been prepared, so we can start laying it. Let's take a break and have a cup of tea.
Yeah, today's progress was a bit slow because we need to cut around the doorframes to ensure a seamless transition with the corridor (which is also being laid with flooring), and it's quite tedious. @user45@twitter.com has been complaining about me all day.
Finally done, but it's a mess! And the assembly instructions for the new bed are terrible too. I can finally sleep well tonight!
The corridor floor and baseboards are still unfinished. The decorators won't come for another month, so we're just making do, with only bare plasterboard in the room.
In the evening, did some simple DIY work, cutting part of the bottom of the doorframe with a chisel and saw, so the floor could fit perfectly below.
The cork mat for the corridor has also been installed.
We laid the corridor floor yesterday! This morning at 5 AM we went to Heathrow Airport to pick up package number 1, then had a nap, and now we can start installing the baseboards for the corridor. Once the glue dries, we'll fill in the gaps.
